%N A107061 a(n) = smallest number m > 0 such that n*prime(n)+m is a prime.
%H A107061 David Cleaver, <a href="/A107061/a107061.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000</a>
%e A107061 a(3) = 2, because 3*prime(3) = 3*5 = 15. The first prime after 15 is 17. So, we want 15+m = 17, therefore m = 2.
%e A107061 a(5) = 4, because 5*prime(5) = 5*11 = 55. The first prime after 55 is 59. So, we want 55+m = 59, therefore m = 4.
%p A107061 f:= proc(n) local t;
%p A107061    t:= n * ithprime(n);
%p A107061    nextprime(t) - t
%p A107061 end proc:
%p A107061 map(f, [$1..100]); # _Robert Israel_, Dec 24 2025
